<DATE>irix-article-020922 22 Sep 2002 - Article Series: IRIX Binary Compatibility, Part 3
<A href="http://www.onlamp.com/">ONLamp.com</a> has published the third
part of Emmanuel Dreyfus's ``<a
href="http://www.onlamp.com/pub/a/bsd/2002/09/12/irix.html">IRIX Binary
Compatibility</a>'' article series.  In this part, Emmanuel explores a few IRIX
oddities. This includes the loading of shared libraries, which has been
implemented inside the IRIX kernel in order to improve performances. In order
to correctly execute dynamic IRIX binaries, the NetBSD kernel needs to
implement the same feature.
<p>
It seems there is no documentation about the way this optimization works,
therefore some reverse engineering has been necessary. This part of the IRIX
binary compatibility on NetBSD series explains how gdb(1), nm(1) and
objdump(1) were used to fully understand the mechanisms involved with IRIX
dynamic linking.

