    href="../Releases/current.html">NetBSD-current</a> to implement the
    newterm and set_term functions.  The changes are quite extensive at a
    fundamental level.
    <p>
    One thing to look out for is that you must update your <tt>vi</tt>
    source and recompile that after installing the new libcurses
    otherwise <tt>vi</tt> will fail.  This is NOT a bug with curses; this
    is a problem with <tt>vi</tt> stealing library function names in certain
    configurations.  In this case <tt>vi</tt> defines its own newterm if
    it has been told there is not one in libcurses.  I have committed the
    config file change for this to the <tt>vi</tt> sources so you should
    be ok.
    <p>
    If anyone has any problems with curses after this change please report
    them with send-pr(1).

